<i>( thunder crashing )</i>

13
00:04:50,890 --> 00:04:53,325
<i>( growls )</i>

14
00:05:11,878 --> 00:05:13,812
<i>( bangs )</i>

15
00:05:49,982 --> 00:05:51,983
<i>( high-pitched tone )</i>

16
00:05:51,985 --> 00:05:54,820
<i>( banging )</i>

17
00:05:54,822 --> 00:05:56,888
<i>( pitch increasing )</i>

18
00:06:16,109 --> 00:06:18,577
Man's voice:
<i>YOU ASK ME TO EXPLAIN</i>
<i>WHY I'M AFRAID</i>

19
00:06:18,579 --> 00:06:20,545
<i>OF A DRAFT OF COOL AIR...</i>

20
00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:31,390
<i>WHY I SHIVER</i>
<i>MORE THAN OTHERS</i>

21
00:06:31,392 --> 00:06:33,058
<i>WHEN I ENTER A COLD ROOM...</i>

22
00:06:35,828 --> 00:06:38,830
<i>WHY I SEEM SICK AND SCARED</i>
<i>WHEN THE CHILL OF EVENING</i>

23
00:06:38,832 --> 00:06:41,500
<i>CREEPS THROUGH THE HEAT</i>
<i>OF A MILD AUTUMN DAY.</i>

24
00:06:50,009 --> 00:06:52,043
<i>THERE ARE THOSE WHO SAY</i>
<i>I RESPOND TO COLD</i>

25
00:06:52,045 --> 00:06:54,045
<i>LIKE SOME DO A BAD SMELL.</i>

26
00:06:55,448 --> 00:06:57,916
<i>AND I'M THE LAST</i>
<i>TO DENY THE IMPRESSION.</i>

27
00:07:04,457 --> 00:07:07,592
<i>WHAT I'LL DO IS TO RELATE</i>
<i>THE MOST HORRIBLE CIRCUMSTANCE</i>

28
00:07:07,594 --> 00:07:10,429
<i>I'VE EVER EXPERIENCED</i>

29
00:07:10,431 --> 00:07:12,998
<i>AND LEAVE IT TO YOU TO JUDGE</i>
<i>WHETHER OR NOT THIS FORMS</i>

30
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,000
<i>A SUITABLE EXPLANATION</i>
<i>OF MY STRANGE BEHAVIOR.</i>

31
00:07:20,039 --> 00:07:23,141
<i>IT IS A MISTAKE TO FANCY</i>
<i>THAT HORROR IS ASSOCIATED</i>

32
00:07:23,143 --> 00:07:27,446
<i>INEXTRICABLY WITH DARKNESS,</i>
<i>SILENCE AND SOLITUDE.</i>

33
00:07:32,852 --> 00:07:35,854
<i>I FOUND IT IN THE GLARE</i>
<i>OF A MID-AFTERNOON,</i>

34
00:07:35,856 --> 00:07:39,991
<i>IN THE DARK CANYONS</i>
<i>THAT LACE THE MALIBU COAST</i>

35
00:07:39,993 --> 00:07:43,795
<i>AND IN THE TEEMING MIDST</i>
<i>OF FADED AND BACKWATER ESTATES.</i>

36
00:07:44,964 --> 00:07:47,966
<i>A BIG HOUSE</i>
<i>BUILT BY BIG DREAMS</i>

37
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:50,936
<i>THAT HAVE LONG GONE</i>
<i>TO REAL-LIFE SHIT,</i>

38
00:07:50,938 --> 00:07:54,806
<i>A HOLLOW PALACE</i>
<i>NOW FORCED TO RENT ROOMS.</i>

39
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:56,908
-  <i>( gear shift clicks )</i>
<i>-</i>  <i>THIS ONLY-IN-L.A.</i>
<i>BOARDING HOUSE</i>

40
00:07:56,910 --> 00:07:59,911
<i>WAS RUN BY A LONG-AGO</i>
<i>TROPHY-WIFE LANDLADY,</i>

41
00:07:59,913 --> 00:08:02,647
<i>HER AUTISTIC DAUGHTER</i>
<i>AND TWO FELLOW BORDERS</i>

42
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:05,250
<i>WHOSE STAY HERE WAS</i>
<i>SIMPLY A BRIEF SOJOURN</i>

43
00:08:05,252 --> 00:08:08,186
<i>OF RESPECTABILITY</i>
<i>ON THEIR WAY TO THE STREETS.</i>

44
00:08:08,188 --> 00:08:09,821
( clicks, whirring )

45
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,694
<i>( car door opens )</i>

46
00:08:16,996 --> 00:08:18,930
<i>( gear shift clicks )</i>

47
00:08:22,134 --> 00:08:24,069
<i>THE PLACE WAS</i>
<i>A FOUR-STORY MANSION</i>

48
00:08:24,071 --> 00:08:27,105
<i>OF CHEAP PLASTER</i>
<i>AND CHEAPER ROOF TILE,</i>

49
00:08:27,107 --> 00:08:29,007
<i>DATING APPARENTLY</i>
<i>FROM THE MID-'80s</i>

50
00:08:29,009 --> 00:08:31,943
<i>AND FITTED WITH MULTI-LEVELS</i>
<i>AND SPLIT-LEVELS</i>

51
00:08:31,945 --> 00:08:35,213
<i>WHOSE STAINED AND SULLIED</i>
<i>SPLENDOR ARGUED A DESCENT</i>

52
00:08:35,215 --> 00:08:38,216
<i>FROM HIGH LEVELS</i>
<i>OF PLENTIFUL CASH AND CREDIT</i>

53
00:08:38,218 --> 00:08:40,919
-  <i>AND A NEW MARRIAGE.</i>
<i>-</i>  <i>( gear shift clicks )</i>

54
00:08:40,921 --> 00:08:45,957
<i>THE RESULT 20 YEARS LATER</i>
<i>STUNK OF A MESSY DIVORCE.</i>

55
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:51,229
-  <i>AT LEAST THE AIR WAS CLEAN..</i>
<i>-</i>  <i>( crows cawing )</i>

56
00:08:51,231 --> 00:08:53,932
<i>...AND THERE WAS NO ONE</i>
<i>TO SEE HOW FAR I'VE FALLEN.</i>

57
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:56,601
<i>IN THE SPRING</i>
<i>I HAD SECURED</i>

58
00:08:56,603 --> 00:08:58,737
<i>SOME DREARY AND UNPROFITABLE</i>
<i>REWRITE WORK</i>

59
00:08:58,739 --> 00:09:01,072
<i>FOR SOME GUTTER-SCUM</i>
<i>PRODUCTION COMPANY.</i>

60
00:09:01,074 --> 00:09:04,042
<i>AFTER THAT WENT BAD--</i>
<i>LIKELY BECAUSE I TOLD</i>
<i>THE PRODUCER</i>

61
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:06,144
<i>WHAT I REALLY THOUGHT</i>
<i>OF HIS WORK...</i>

62
00:09:06,146 --> 00:09:08,280
Woman:
CHARLIE BAXTER.

63
00:09:08,282 --> 00:09:10,982
- Charlie: MRS. HAYWARD.
- THAT'S RIGHT.

64
00:09:10,984 --> 00:09:15,887
-  <i>...AND BEING UNABLE TO PAY</i>
<i>ANY SUBSTANTIAL RENT...</i>
<i>- KEEP GOING AROUND.</i>

65
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:18,990
- OKAY.
- <i>...I BEGAN DRIFTING FROM ONE</i>
<i>CHEAP APARTMENT TO ANOTHER</i>

66
00:09:18,992 --> 00:09:21,226
<i>UNTIL I WAS DOWN</i>
<i>TO LOOKING FOR A ROOM.</i>

67
00:09:21,228 --> 00:09:24,996
<i>I HAD HOPED TO FIND SOMEPLACE</i>
<i>WHERE I COULD PUSH THROUGH</i>
<i>MY WRITER'S BLOCK</i>

68
00:09:24,998 --> 00:09:29,234
- <i>AND FINISH</i>
<i>MY OWN GREAT SCREENPLAY.</i>
<i>- WAS IT EASY TO FIND?</i>

69
00:09:29,236 --> 00:09:32,938
Charlie's voice:
<i>BUT RIGHT THEN, I NEEDED</i>
<i>A PLACE THAT WAS CHEAP...</i>

70
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:35,006
PLEASE, COME ON IN.

71
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:37,742
<i>...BUT CLEAN AND QUIET.</i>

72
00:09:38,878 --> 00:09:41,613
- Charlie: <i>NICE PLACE.</i>
<i>-</i>  <i>( door closes )</i>

73
00:09:41,615 --> 00:09:44,182
Charlie's voice:
<i>IN THE ROOMS, LARGE AND LOFTY</i>

74
00:09:44,184 --> 00:09:47,118
<i>AND DECORATED</i>
<i>WITH SCHIZOPHRENIC TASTE</i>

75
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:49,588
<i>AND RIDICULOUS KITSCH,</i>

76
00:09:49,590 --> 00:09:52,023
<i>THERE LINGERED</i>
<i>A DEPRESSING MUSTINESS</i>

77
00:09:52,025 --> 00:09:56,328
<i>AND A HINT OF OBSCURE...</i>
<i>SOMETHING.</i>

78
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:59,331
<i>SOMETHING I COULDN'T</i>
<i>QUITE PLACE AT THAT MOMENT.</i>

79
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:01,633
Mrs. Hayward:
IT'S SO BIG.

80
00:10:01,635 --> 00:10:04,736
HARD TO KEEP UP
WITH JUST MYSELF
AND MY DAUGHTER.

81
00:10:04,738 --> 00:10:06,838
STILL, YOU'VE DONE WONDERS.

82
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:11,042
- I LIKE THE ANIMALS.
- AREN'T THEY PRECIOUS?

83
00:10:11,044 --> 00:10:13,812
THEY WANDERED
ONTO THE PROPERTY ONE DAY.

84
00:10:13,814 --> 00:10:16,047
FIRST THE GOATS,
THEN THE SHEEP.

85
00:10:16,049 --> 00:10:18,650
YOU'RE TRYING
TO GET THEM TO EAT
SOME OF THAT TALL GRASS.

86
00:10:18,652 --> 00:10:21,052
THAT WAS THE HOPE.
I'M A LITTLE BRITTLE

87
00:10:21,054 --> 00:10:22,854
TO BE WEED WHACKING
THE PROPERTY.

88
00:10:22,856 --> 00:10:24,923
- HAVE TO, YOU KNOW.
- WILD FIRES, RIGHT?

89
00:10:24,925 --> 00:10:27,726
THAT'S RIGHT.
BIG FINE IF YOU DON'T.

90
00:10:27,728 --> 00:10:29,260
WELL, MAYBE I CAN
HELP YOU THERE.

91
00:10:29,262 --> 00:10:32,130
YOU WIELD
A MEAN WHACKER, CHARLIE?

92
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,101
I LOVE THE FLOORS.

93
00:10:36,103 --> 00:10:39,170
Charlie's voice:
<i>THE WOOD WAS NOT</i>
<i>EXACTLY SPECIAL,</i>

94
00:10:39,172 --> 00:10:41,239
<i>BUT THE FLOORS WERE CLEAN.</i>

95
00:10:41,241 --> 00:10:43,908
Mrs. Hayward:
<i>IF YOU DON'T REQUIRE</i>
<i>A CERTAIN MEAL,</i>

96
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:47,679
I'D APPRECIATE THE NOTICE
SO I DON'T OVER-PREPARE.

97
00:10:47,681 --> 00:10:50,782
THE FAMILY ROOM IS
A COMMON ROOM.

98
00:10:50,784 --> 00:10:52,751
WE DO HAVE SATELLITE.

99
00:10:52,753 --> 00:10:54,719
WOW.  SATELLITE.

100
00:10:54,721 --> 00:10:57,022
I DATE THE GUY
AT THE LOCAL RADIO SHACK.

101
00:10:57,024 --> 00:10:59,090
HE GIVES ME
THE PROGRAMS FOR FREE.

102
00:10:59,092 --> 00:11:03,094
- GREAT.
- ANYTHING WE CAN DO
TO MAKE ENDS MEET.

103
00:11:03,096 --> 00:11:06,264
- IT ALL HELPS.
- EXACTLY.

104
00:11:06,266 --> 00:11:08,667
YOU UNDERSTAND.

105
00:11:08,669 --> 00:11:10,969
YOU ARE
IN THE BUSINESS.

106
00:11:12,171 --> 00:11:14,205
UH, WHAT ABOUT LAUNDRY?

107
00:11:14,207 --> 00:11:16,775
IT'S $10 EXTRA PER LOAD,

108
00:11:16,777 --> 00:11:19,110
AND I DON'T DO
ANYTHING EXOTIC.

109
00:11:19,112 --> 00:11:22,013
POCKETS HAVE TO BE CLEAR.
IS THAT UNDERSTOOD?

110
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:24,883
THERE'S A LAUNDROMAT IN MALIBU
IF THAT'S TOO STEEP.

111
00:11:24,885 --> 00:11:28,119
( smacks lips )
SOUNDS REASONABLE.

112
00:11:28,121 --> 00:11:31,056
- I THINK SO.
- Charlie's voice:
<i>THE TOUR CONTINUED.</i>

113
00:11:32,725 --> 00:11:36,027
<i>AS IT TURNED OUT,</i>
<i>THE LINEN CHANGE WAS</i>
<i>TOLERABLY REGULAR</i>

114
00:11:36,029 --> 00:11:39,397
<i>AND THE HOT WATER</i>
<i>NOT TOO OFTEN COLD</i>
<i>OR TURNED OFF,</i>

115
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:42,133
<i>SO THAT I CAME</i>
<i>TO REGARD IT</i>

116
00:11:42,135 --> 00:11:44,369
<i>AS AT LEAST</i>
<i>A BEARABLE PLACE</i>
<i>TO HUNKER DOWN</i>

117
00:11:44,371 --> 00:11:46,337
<i>UNTIL I MIGHT</i>
<i>REALLY LIVE AGAIN.</i>

118
00:11:46,339 --> 00:11:48,440
YOU WILL SHARE
THIS BATHROOM.

119
00:11:48,442 --> 00:11:51,209
DON'T GO UP THERE,
ALL RIGHT?

120
00:11:54,013 --> 00:11:56,781
AND IF YOU NEED
MORE TOWELS,

121
00:11:56,783 --> 00:11:59,150
THEY'RE RIGHT
IN HERE, OKAY?

122
00:11:59,152 --> 00:12:01,219
AND, WELL,
HERE'S YOUR ROOM.

123
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:07,392
Charlie's voice:
<i>AS FOR MRS. HAYWARD,</i>

124
00:12:07,394 --> 00:12:10,161
<i>SHE DIDN'T ANNOY ME</i>
<i>WITH THE GOSSIP</i>

125
00:12:10,163 --> 00:12:14,032
<i>OR WITH CRITICISMS</i>
<i>OF EXCESSIVE ELECTRIC USE</i>
<i>IN MY THIRD-FLOOR ROOM.</i>

126
00:12:14,034 --> 00:12:15,333
YEAH, THAT'S GREAT.

127
00:12:15,335 --> 00:12:17,402
( chatting continues )

128
00:12:19,506 --> 00:12:23,975
- <i>DO YOU NEED</i>
<i>SOME HELP OR--</i>
<i>- NO NO NO, I'M OKAY.</i>

129
00:12:23,977 --> 00:12:25,744
-  <i>OKAY, GREAT.</i>
<i>- THANK YOU. ( mutters )</i>

130
00:12:25,746 --> 00:12:28,113
- ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT ME TO--
-  <i>NO NO NO.</i>

131
00:12:28,115 --> 00:12:30,181
- <i>THANK YOU.</i>
<i>-</i> <i>( floor creaking )</i>

132
00:12:30,183 --> 00:12:32,250
<i>( woman coughing )</i>

133
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:46,030
Charlie's voice:
<i>AND MY FELLOW LODGERS WERE</i>

134
00:12:46,032 --> 00:12:49,200
<i>AS QUIET AND UNCOMMUNICATIVE</i>
<i>AS ONE MIGHT DESIRE...</i>

135
00:12:50,369 --> 00:12:53,004
BEING MOSTLY DOWN-ON-THEIR-LUCK
<i>INDUSTRY TYPES</i>

136
00:12:53,006 --> 00:12:55,473
<i>A LITTLE ABOVE THE COARSEST</i>
<i>AND CRUDEST GRADE</i>

137
00:12:55,475 --> 00:12:58,009
<i>OF STUDIO PRODUCER</i>
<i>OR DIRECTOR.</i>

138
00:12:59,044 --> 00:13:00,879
<i>ONLY THE DIN</i>
<i>OF GOATS BAAA-ING</i>

139
00:13:00,881 --> 00:13:03,314
<i>BELOW MY WINDOW PROVED</i>
<i>A SERIOUS ANNOYANCE.</i>

140
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,241
<i>I'D BEEN THERE TWO DAYS</i>

141
00:13:30,243 --> 00:13:32,977
<i>WHEN THE FIRST</i>
<i>ODD INCIDENT OCCURRED.</i>

142
00:13:34,246 --> 00:13:35,980
<i>ONE MORNING</i>
<i>AT ABOUT 7:00,</i>

143
00:13:35,982 --> 00:13:38,249
<i>I HEARD SOMETHING SPILL</i>
<i>ON THE FLOOR...</i>

144
00:13:38,251 --> 00:13:39,484
<i>( clattering )</i>

145
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:41,452
<i>...KIND OF</i>
<i>A SPLATTERING SOUND,</i>

146
00:13:41,454 --> 00:13:44,322
<i>AND BECAME SUDDENLY AWARE</i>
<i>THAT I'D BEEN SMELLING</i>

147
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:47,258
<i>THE PUNGENT ODOR</i>
<i>OF SOMETHING FOUL</i>
<i>FOR A WHILE.</i>

148
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:50,328
- <i>( faint whirring )</i>
<i>- ( sniffing )</i>

149
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:54,032
<i>( thrumming )</i>

150
00:14:03,976 --> 00:14:06,211
<i>THE WALL WAS WET,</i>

151
00:14:06,213 --> 00:14:08,046
<i>LIKE CONDENSATION...</i>

152
00:14:08,048 --> 00:14:09,914
<i>AND COOL--</i>

153
00:14:09,916 --> 00:14:11,449
<i>UNNATURALLY COOL.</i>

154
00:14:11,451 --> 00:14:14,352
<i>A CHILL REACHED DEEP</i>
<i>TO MY BONES.</i>

155
00:14:18,991 --> 00:14:21,292
<i>( crows cawing )</i>

156
00:14:21,294 --> 00:14:23,361
<i>( birds chirping )</i>

157
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:27,065
<i>I HADN'T MET EITHER</i>
<i>OF MY FELLOW LODGERS</i>

158
00:14:27,067 --> 00:14:29,133
<i>AS THEY KEPT ODD HOURS</i>

159
00:14:29,135 --> 00:14:31,636
<i>AND ONE NEVER SEEMED</i>
<i>TO LEAVE HIS OR HER ROOM.</i>

160
00:14:31,638 --> 00:14:35,240
<i>IF THEY TOOK MEALS,</i>
<i>IT WAS AT PROBABLY</i>
<i>AT FIRST CALL,</i>

161
00:14:35,242 --> 00:14:37,308
<i>SINCE I WAS FINDING MYSELF</i>
<i>JUST MAKING IT</i>

162
00:14:37,310 --> 00:14:39,444
<i>BEFORE THE KITCHEN CLOSED.</i>

163
00:14:39,446 --> 00:14:41,312
<i>I KNEW THE NEIGHBOR</i>
<i>TO MY LEFT WAS</i>

164
00:14:41,314 --> 00:14:44,315
- <i>A MAN NAMED ARNOLD DELTOID.</i>
<i>-</i> <i>( whirring, hissing )</i>

165
00:14:44,317 --> 00:14:47,318
<i>MRS. HAYWARD SAID</i>
<i>DELTOID HAD BEEN</i>
<i>AN ANIMATOR AT DISNEY</i>

166
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,487
<i>DURING THE STUDIO'S GOLDEN AGE</i>
<i>BACK IN THE '50s...</i>

167
00:14:49,489 --> 00:14:51,322
THERE'S SOMETHING LEAKING
IN MY ROOM FROM--

168
00:14:51,324 --> 00:14:53,324
<i>...BEFORE EVERYTHING</i>
<i>BECAME DIGITAL,</i>

169
00:14:53,326 --> 00:14:56,060
<i>BEFORE HE GOT</i>
<i>FORCIBLY RETIRED.</i>

170
00:14:56,062 --> 00:14:58,263
<i>NOW HE WAS HOLED UP HERE,</i>

171
00:14:58,265 --> 00:15:00,331
-  <i>DESPERATELY TRYING</i>
<i>TO LEARN SOFTWARE...</i>
<i>- HELLO?</i>

172
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:03,534
<i>...THAT WOULD ALLOW</i>
<i>HIM TO EARN A LIVING</i>
<i>IN THE 21st CENTURY.</i>

173
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:08,172
<i>THE OTHER LODGER</i>
<i>WAS A MYSTERY.</i>

174
00:15:08,174 --> 00:15:11,242
<i>MRS. HAYWARD HAD DEFLECTED</i>
<i>ALL MY QUESTIONS,</i>

175
00:15:11,244 --> 00:15:13,344
<i>WHICH JUST JACKED UP</i>
<i>MY CURIOSITY.</i>

176
00:15:13,346 --> 00:15:16,347
<i>THE LODGER NEVER LEFT</i>
<i>THE ROOM, AS FAR AS I KNEW.</i>

177
00:15:16,349 --> 00:15:20,485
<i>MRS. HAYWARD DELIVERED</i>
<i>THREE SQUARES TO HIM DAILY.</i>

178
00:15:20,487 --> 00:15:23,354
<i>A COUPLE TIMES I HEARD</i>
<i>WHAT SOUNDED LIKE A COUGH.</i>

179
00:15:23,356 --> 00:15:29,360
<i>SOMETHING LIKE</i>
<i>AN AIR CONDITIONER</i>
<i>GOING FULL BLAST.</i>

180
00:15:29,362 --> 00:15:31,362
<i>BUT MORE...</i>

181
00:15:31,364 --> 00:15:33,431
<i>( mechanical hissing )</i>

182
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:45,443
<i>( silverware clinks )</i>

183
00:15:46,947 --> 00:15:51,683
- OUTSIDE
BY SIDE OF THE HOUSE.
- <i>( thrumming continues )</i>

184
00:15:51,685 --> 00:15:54,152
Charlie's voice:
<i>ANXIOUS TO ALERT MRS. HAYWARD</i>

185
00:15:54,154 --> 00:15:56,521
<i>ABOUT WHAT WAS</i>
<i>GOING ON IN THE ROOM</i>
<i>AT THE END OF THE HALL,</i>

186
00:15:56,523 --> 00:15:58,957
<i>AND, TO BE HONEST,</i>

187
00:15:58,959 --> 00:16:01,592
<i>TO LEARN A LITTLE MORE</i>
<i>ABOUT THIS MYSTERY LODGER...</i>

188
00:16:01,594 --> 00:16:04,729
<i>( birds chirping, cawing )</i>

189
00:16:04,731 --> 00:16:06,397
<i>...PUSHED BY MY CURIOSITY,</i>

190
00:16:06,399 --> 00:16:08,733
<i>I HURRIED OUTSIDE</i>
<i>TO FIND THE LANDLADY.</i>

191
00:16:13,405 --> 00:16:14,739
- OH! ( gasps )
- JEEZ!

192
00:16:14,741 --> 00:16:16,307
OH, GOOD MORNING,
CHARLIE.

193
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:18,276
HAD BREAKFAST YET?
IT ENDS IN 10 MINUTES.

194
00:16:18,278 --> 00:16:20,311
YEAH, THANKS, MRS. HAYWARD,
I'LL GET RIGHT ON THAT.

195
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:24,015
THERE'S BEEN A LITTLE ACCIDENT.
NOT TO WORRY, CHARLIE.

196
00:16:24,017 --> 00:16:26,517
WE'RE TAKING
CARE OF IT RIGHT NOW.
SORRY IF IT DISTURBED YOU.

197
00:16:31,423 --> 00:16:32,423
OH!  JEEZ!

198
00:16:32,425 --> 00:16:34,492
( exhales deeply )

199
00:16:37,463 --> 00:16:39,263
HI.

200
00:16:51,443 --> 00:16:52,543
<i>( door opens )</i>

201
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:57,348
<i>( thrumming continues )</i>

202
00:17:18,437 --> 00:17:20,104
IT'S GETTING WORSE.

203
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:25,510
- Charlie: <i>WHAT?</i>
<i>- THE DOCTOR'S ACCIDENTS.</i>

204
00:17:31,817 --> 00:17:34,652
- <i>( footsteps overhead )</i>
<i>- WHAT KIND OF ACCIDENTS?</i>

205
00:17:34,654 --> 00:17:36,754
SPILLS,
BROKEN BOTTLES.

206
00:17:39,191 --> 00:17:42,060
I ONLY HEAR IT.
NEVER ACTUALLY SEEN THE DOCTOR

207
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:45,296
OR THE INSIDE
OF HIS... ROOM.

208
00:17:46,465 --> 00:17:47,698
MUST PAY
A HEALTHY RENT TO GET

209
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:50,334
- THAT KIND OF SERVICE.
- ( chuckles )

210
00:17:50,336 --> 00:17:53,538
WHAT'S RENT MONEY
TO A DOCTOR, ANYWAY?

211
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:56,507
<i>EXACTLY.  WHY WOULD</i>
<i>A DOCTOR RENT A ROOM?</i>

212
00:17:59,311 --> 00:18:02,180
DON'T KNOW
AND FRANKLY, DON'T CARE.
IT'S NONE OF MY BUSINESS.

213
00:18:02,182 --> 00:18:04,615
THE DOCTOR WAS ALREADY HERE
BEFORE I ARRIVED.

214
00:18:09,521 --> 00:18:12,457
- MRS. HAYWARD EVER
TALK ABOUT HIM?
- <i>NOPE.</i>

215
00:18:12,459 --> 00:18:15,159
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF IT'S A HIM OR A HER.

216
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:31,642
SHE SAID YOU WERE
A SCREENWRITER?

217
00:18:32,678 --> 00:18:35,346
YEAH, I USED
TO SAY THAT...

218
00:18:36,648 --> 00:18:38,449
BUT NOT NOW.

219
00:18:44,890 --> 00:18:47,158
WHAT ARE YOU NOW?

220
00:18:48,494 --> 00:18:50,194
WANNABE.

221
00:18:50,196 --> 00:18:52,530
( laughs )
AT LEAST YOU'RE HONEST.

222
00:19:00,906 --> 00:19:03,808
<i>- ( glass shatters )</i>
<i>- ( bangs )</i>

223
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:05,643
<i>( clatters )</i>

224
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:09,547
<i>( woman coughing )</i>

225
00:19:11,517 --> 00:19:13,451
Arnold:
<i>YOU'LL GET USED TO IT.</i>

226
00:19:17,856 --> 00:19:19,624
WHAT'S THE STORY
ON THE GIRL?

227
00:19:21,360 --> 00:19:22,760
AUTISTIC,

228
00:19:22,762 --> 00:19:26,397
BUT IT SEEMS
TO COME AND GO.

229
00:19:28,534 --> 00:19:30,668
AUTISM DOESN'T
COME AND GO.

230
00:19:35,474 --> 00:19:37,542
( humphs )

231
00:19:44,216 --> 00:19:46,651
THE EGGS SEEM
A LITTLE RUNNY TODAY.

232
00:19:51,557 --> 00:19:53,424
<i>( squishes )</i>

233
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:06,938
( breathing deeply )

234
00:20:10,342 --> 00:20:12,376
<i>( mechanical hissing )</i>

235
00:20:13,312 --> 00:20:15,379
<i>( thrumming )</i>

236
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:20,685
- <i>( keys jingling )</i>
<i>- HEY.</i>

237
00:20:20,687 --> 00:20:24,422
- LEAVING?
- ( lock clicks )

238
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:39,670
- CHARLIE.
- THAT'S RIGHT.

239
00:20:39,672 --> 00:20:41,606
AND YOU'RE ESTELLA.

240
00:20:43,475 --> 00:20:46,877
CHAR-LEE.  CHAR-LEEE.

241
00:20:54,453 --> 00:20:56,020
( sighs )

242
00:20:56,022 --> 00:20:58,689
<i>THE DOCTOR SPILLED</i>
<i>SOME CHEMICALS.</i>

243
00:20:58,691 --> 00:21:00,491
THE ODOR WILL
BE GONE SHORTLY.

244
00:21:00,493 --> 00:21:02,693
I CAN DIG UP
SOME DEODORIZER FOR YOU.

245
00:21:02,695 --> 00:21:04,629
- NO, IT'S FINE.
- I'M SO SORRY.

246
00:21:04,631 --> 00:21:06,797
THE DOCTOR HAS BEEN ILL,
YET THE WORK CONTINUES,

247
00:21:06,799 --> 00:21:08,733
<i>SO THERE ARE ACCIDENTS.</i>

248
00:21:08,735 --> 00:21:12,003
- ( sighs deeply )
- HE WORKS IN HIS ROOM?

249
00:21:12,005 --> 00:21:14,305
THE DOCTOR IS
BEDBOUND NOW.

250
00:21:14,307 --> 00:21:16,507
WELL, WOULDN'T THE DOCTOR
BE BETTER OFF--

251
00:21:16,509 --> 00:21:19,443
IN A HOSPITAL?
WELL, YES, BUT THE DOCTOR
WON'T HEAR OF IT.

252
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:21,712
<i>THE DOCTOR KEEPS SAYING</i>
<i>THAT'S WHERE PEOPLE</i>
<i>GO TO DIE.</i>

253
00:21:21,714 --> 00:21:24,949
THE DOCTOR BELIEVES IN
AN EXPERIMENTAL TREATMENT--

254
00:21:24,951 --> 00:21:28,019
QUITE RADICAL,
SELF-ADMINISTERED
AROUND THE CLOCK.

255
00:21:28,021 --> 00:21:30,288
THE DOCTOR'S ROOM HAS
TO BE HAS TO BE KEPT

256
00:21:30,290 --> 00:21:33,591
BELOW 55째
AT ALL TIMES.

257
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:36,727
-  <i>WHAT'S THE TREATMENT?</i>
<i>- ( sighs )</i>

258
00:21:36,729 --> 00:21:38,663
I ONLY KNOW THAT IT
INVOLVES KEEPING

259
00:21:38,665 --> 00:21:40,865
THE TEMPERATURE LOW
AND INJECTIONS.

260
00:21:40,867 --> 00:21:43,534
MANY INJECTIONS.

261
00:21:43,536 --> 00:21:46,904
<i>THE DOCTOR WAS A FAMOUS</i>
<i>NEUROSURGEON AT U.C.L.A.</i>

262
00:21:46,906 --> 00:21:50,908
THE DOCTOR IS
DOING IT ALONE?

263
00:21:50,910 --> 00:21:54,745
THE DOCTOR ALLOWS ESTELLA
TO ASSIST, NO ONE ELSE.

264
00:21:54,747 --> 00:21:57,682
ESTELLA?
BUT SHE'S AUTISTIC.

265
00:21:58,617 --> 00:21:59,684
THAT'S RIGHT.

266
00:22:01,420 --> 00:22:04,488
Charlie's voice:
<i>MRS. HAYWARD DISAPPEARED</i>
<i>AND ALL WAS QUIET AGAIN.</i>

267
00:22:04,490 --> 00:22:06,824
<i>I RETURNED</i>
<i>TO MY ROOM.</i>

268
00:22:12,431 --> 00:22:14,498
<i>( thrumming continues )</i>

269
00:22:31,049 --> 00:22:33,017
<i>THE LIQUID</i>
<i>HAD CEASED TO DRIP.</i>

270
00:22:33,019 --> 00:22:34,785
<i>I HEARD THE LANDLADY'S</i>

271
00:22:34,787 --> 00:22:36,721
<i>HEAVY FOOTSTEPS</i>
<i>ON THE FLOOR ABOVE ME,</i>

272
00:22:36,723 --> 00:22:38,656
<i>ALONG WITH</i>
<i>HER ISSUING COMMANDS</i>

273
00:22:38,658 --> 00:22:41,692
<i>TO HER</i> MOSTLY
<i>AUTISTIC DAUGHTER.</i>

274
00:22:45,063 --> 00:22:49,433
<i>A DAUGHTER I FOUND</i>
<i>TO HAVE A CERTAIN</i>
<i>FASCINATION AND APPEAL.</i>

275
00:22:49,435 --> 00:22:51,736
<i>( fly buzzing )</i>

276
00:22:55,607 --> 00:22:59,410
<i>HMM.  AUTISTIC HOTTIE.</i>

277
00:22:59,412 --> 00:23:01,746
<i>WOULD THAT BE</i>
<i>AN OXYMORON?</i>

278
00:23:05,617 --> 00:23:09,520
<i>SUDDENLY I WAS</i>
<i>AWARE OF A FEELING</i>
<i>I HAD LONG MISSED.</i>

279
00:23:10,655 --> 00:23:12,923
<i>I WAS DRAWN</i>
<i>TO THE PAGE.</i>

280
00:23:50,028 --> 00:23:52,096
<i>( crows cawing )</i>

281
00:24:02,874 --> 00:24:06,110
- <i>( heart beating )</i>
<i>- ( exhales )</i>

282
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:17,988
<i>ESTELLA FASCINATED ME.</i>

283
00:24:20,025 --> 00:24:23,093
<i>SHE WAS LIKE A DREAM THAT</i>
<i>ONE COULDN'T QUITE TOUCH.</i>

284
00:24:27,098 --> 00:24:28,966
<i>DAMN THAT AUTISM.</i>

285
00:24:31,203 --> 00:24:33,471
<i>( birds chirping )</i>

286
00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:38,008
STOP.

287
00:24:38,010 --> 00:24:39,910
STOP.

288
00:24:39,912 --> 00:24:41,545
- STOP!
- I'M SORRY.  I--

289
00:24:43,715 --> 00:24:45,783
( laughing )

290
00:24:52,958 --> 00:24:55,626
CHAR-LEE.  CHARL-EE.

291
00:24:55,628 --> 00:24:59,830
- I-I-- I--
I LIKE THE SOUND.
- <i>( goat bleats )</i>

292
00:24:59,832 --> 00:25:02,933
CHAR-LEE.

293
00:25:02,935 --> 00:25:05,135
I LIKE IT TOO...

294
00:25:05,137 --> 00:25:07,571
COMING FROM YOU.

295
00:25:15,013 --> 00:25:17,081
( laughs )

296
00:25:19,618 --> 00:25:21,785
ESTELLA!

297
00:25:21,787 --> 00:25:23,654
<i>I NEED YOU, HONEY!</i>

298
00:25:51,650 --> 00:25:54,718
STAY AWAY
FROM MY DAUGHTER,
MR. BAXTER.

299
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:56,854
WE MAY BE DESPERATE,
BUT NOT EVERYTHING

300
00:25:56,856 --> 00:26:00,891
- OR OTHERWISE.
- ( stammers )
I DIDN'T MEAN ANYTHING.

301
00:26:00,893 --> 00:26:02,860
- LIKE HELL YOU DIDN'T.
- LOOK--

302
00:26:02,862 --> 00:26:05,696
MAYBE I DON'T DO
THE BACKGROUND CHECKING
I SHOULD

303
00:26:05,698 --> 00:26:08,165
AND I KNOW THE TYPE
THAT NEEDS WHAT I GOT,

304
00:26:08,167 --> 00:26:10,067
BUT YOU ARE
WAY OUT OF LINE.

305
00:26:10,069 --> 00:26:13,003
- PLEASE, MRS. HAYWARD--
- I WANT YOU OUT OF HERE
IN AN HOUR.

306
00:26:13,005 --> 00:26:15,573
YOU'VE GOT ONE HOUR
BEFORE I CALL THE POLICE.

307
00:26:15,575 --> 00:26:18,008
- IS THAT CLEAR TO YOU?
- YES.

308
00:26:19,778 --> 00:26:22,012
I'M SORRY,
MRS. HAYWARD.

309
00:26:22,014 --> 00:26:24,014
ESTELLA'S AUTISM
INTERESTED ME.  I--

310
00:26:24,016 --> 00:26:27,017
IT'S THE WAY THAT
SOMETIMES SHE'S AFFECTED
AND SOMETIMES--

311
00:26:27,019 --> 00:26:28,886
THANKS TO DR. SHOCKNER.

312
00:26:29,955 --> 00:26:31,622
YOU'VE GOT ONE HOUR.

313
00:26:31,624 --> 00:26:33,023
<i>( heart beating )</i>

314
00:26:40,031 --> 00:26:42,099
<i>( static )</i>

315
00:26:56,181 --> 00:26:58,649
Charlie's voice:
<i>DR. SHOCKNER I HAD</i>
<i>NEVER HEARD,</i>

316
00:26:58,651 --> 00:27:02,052
<i>EXCEPT FOR CERTAIN SOUNDS LIKE</i>
<i>AN AIR-CONDITIONER MECHANISM</i>

317
00:27:02,054 --> 00:27:04,054
<i>AND WHAT SOUNDED LIKE A PUMP.</i>

318
00:27:04,056 --> 00:27:06,056
<i>( hissing, whirring )</i>

319
00:27:06,058 --> 00:27:08,726
<i>I WONDERED FOR A MOMENT</i>
<i>ABOUT WHAT STRANGE ILLNESS</i>

320
00:27:08,728 --> 00:27:13,063
<i>THIS DOCTOR MIGHT HAVE,</i>
<i>AND WHETHER SHOCKNER'S</i>
<i>STUBBORN REFUSAL</i>

321
00:27:13,065 --> 00:27:17,901
<i>OF OUTSIDE AID WERE</i>
<i>THE RESULT OF A RATHER</i>
<i>INSANE ECCENTRICITY.</i>

322
00:27:18,870 --> 00:27:20,070
<i>( heartbeat continues )</i>

323
00:27:20,072 --> 00:27:22,139
<i>THERE IS, I REFLECTED,</i>

324
00:27:23,108 --> 00:27:25,309
<i>AN INFINITE AMOUNT</i>
<i>OF MADNESS IN THE MIND</i>

325
00:27:25,311 --> 00:27:27,678
<i>OF A ONCE POWERFUL</i>
<i>AND WEALTHY PERSON</i>

326
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:29,413
<i>WHO HAS FALLEN DOWN</i>
<i>IN THE WORLD.</i>

327
00:27:32,751 --> 00:27:35,052
<i>I MIGHT NEVER</i>
<i>HAVE MET DR. SHOCKNER</i>

328
00:27:35,054 --> 00:27:37,755
<i>EXCEPT FOR THE HEART ATTACK</i>
<i>THAT SUDDENLY STRUCK ME</i>

329
00:27:37,757 --> 00:27:40,290
<i>THAT AFTERNOON AS I PREPARED</i>
<i>TO VACATE MY ROOM.</i>

330
00:27:40,292 --> 00:27:43,727
<i>( heartbeat continues )</i>

331
00:27:46,231 --> 00:27:49,166
( thuds )

332
00:27:50,969 --> 00:27:52,903
<i>I KNEW I WAS</i>
<i>IN TROUBLE,</i>

333
00:27:52,905 --> 00:27:55,706
<i>AND I KNEW THERE WAS</i>
<i>NO TIME TO WASTE.</i>

334
00:27:57,709 --> 00:27:59,209
( thuds )

335
00:28:07,952 --> 00:28:09,453
<i>MY BRAIN WAS FRYING.</i>

336
00:28:09,455 --> 00:28:12,056
<i>MY CHEST WAS EXPLODING.</i>

337
00:28:12,058 --> 00:28:14,158
<i>( heartbeat continues )</i>

338
00:28:16,094 --> 00:28:18,328
<i>I REALIZED</i>
<i>I WAS HAVING A STROKE</i>

339
00:28:18,330 --> 00:28:22,199
- <i>AS A COMPANION</i>
<i>TO MY HEART FAILURE.</i>
<i>- ( distorted breathing )</i>

340
00:28:36,347 --> 00:28:38,415
<i>( heartbeat continues )</i>

341
00:28:39,884 --> 00:28:42,753
<i>I REMEMBER THINKING</i>
<i>HOW SURREAL IT ALL WAS.</i>

342
00:28:42,755 --> 00:28:45,089
<i>I THINK,</i>
<i>BUT I CAN'T BE POSITIVE,</i>

343
00:28:45,091 --> 00:28:49,927
<i>THAT I HEARD</i>
<i>HUMMING AS I SAW</i>
<i>THE WHITE LIGHT OF HEAVEN.</i>

344
00:28:49,929 --> 00:28:52,930
<i>OR WAS IT THE GLOW</i>
<i>FROM THE FURNACES OF HELL?</i>

345
00:28:54,165 --> 00:28:56,767
<i>IN THAT MOMENT</i>
<i>IT DIDN'T MATTER.</i>

346
00:28:58,136 --> 00:29:01,171
<i>CHARLIE BAXTER HAD FOUND</i>
<i>HIS MOMENT OF GRACE</i>

347
00:29:01,173 --> 00:29:04,208
<i>AND IT WAS SCORED</i>
<i>BY THE MOST BEAUTIFUL HUMMING</i>

348
00:29:04,210 --> 00:29:05,909
<i>HE HAD EVER HEARD.</i>

349
00:29:10,181 --> 00:29:12,449
<i>( hissing )</i>

350
00:29:18,323 --> 00:29:20,190
<i>AFTER A MOMENT,</i>
<i>I COULD HEAR</i>

351
00:29:20,192 --> 00:29:22,760
<i>WHAT I THINK WAS</i>
<i>THE SOUND OF A FOOTFALL,</i>

352
00:29:22,762 --> 00:29:25,529
<i>THEN THERE CAME AN OPENING</i>
<i>OF THE DOOR IN FRONT OF ME.</i>

353
00:29:25,531 --> 00:29:28,499
( creaking )

354
00:29:28,501 --> 00:29:31,001
<i>A RUSH OF COOL AIR</i>
<i>GREETED ME,</i>

355
00:29:31,003 --> 00:29:34,204
<i>AND THOUGH THE DAY</i>
<i>WAS ONE OF THE HOTTEST</i>
<i>OF THAT SUMMER...</i>

356
00:29:34,206 --> 00:29:36,273
- <i>( distorted footsteps )</i>
<i>-</i> <i>...I SHIVERED.</i>

357
00:29:38,176 --> 00:29:41,545
<i>I NOW SAW A TABLE OF BOTTLES</i>
<i>AND MACHINES AND SYRINGES</i>

358
00:29:41,547 --> 00:29:43,280
<i>WHICH MRS. HAYWARD</i>
<i>HAD MENTIONED.</i>

359
00:29:43,282 --> 00:29:45,983
<i>THIS WAS THE LABORATORY</i>
<i>OF THE DOCTOR.</i>

360
00:29:45,985 --> 00:29:48,452
<i>DR. SHOCKNER</i>
<i>MOST CERTAINLY WAS</i>

361
00:29:48,454 --> 00:29:51,889
<i>A PERSON OF EDUCATION,</i>
<i>TASTE AND WEALTH.</i>

362
00:29:51,891 --> 00:29:53,824
( woman speaks )

363
00:30:00,231 --> 00:30:02,933
<i>THEN A FIGURE</i>
<i>APPEARED OVER ME.</i>

364
00:30:02,935 --> 00:30:06,236
<i>THE FIGURE WAS SHORT</i>
<i>BUT EXQUISITELY PROPORTIONED</i>

365
00:30:06,238 --> 00:30:10,174
<i>AND WORE A SOMEWHAT FORMAL</i>
<i>RODEO DRIVE WARDROBE</i>

366
00:30:10,176 --> 00:30:12,442
<i>OF PERFECT CUT AND FIT.</i>

367
00:30:14,245 --> 00:30:16,246
<i>NEVERTHELESS,</i>

368
00:30:16,248 --> 00:30:19,383
<i>AS I SAW DR. SHOCKNER</i>
<i>IN THAT BLAST OF COOL AIR,</i>

369
00:30:19,385 --> 00:30:21,952
<i>I FELT A REPUGNANCE</i>

370
00:30:21,954 --> 00:30:25,222
<i>WHICH NOTHING</i>
<i>IN THE DOCTOR'S LOOK</i>
<i>COULD JUSTIFY.</i>

371
00:30:26,491 --> 00:30:29,326
<i>ONLY SHOCKNER'S</i>
<i>FLAT ALABASTER COMPLEXION</i>

372
00:30:29,328 --> 00:30:33,263
<i>AND COLDNESS OF TOUCH</i>
<i>COULD HAVE EXPLAINED</i>
<i>WHAT I WAS FEELING.</i>

373
00:30:33,265 --> 00:30:36,266
<i>AND EVEN THESE THINGS SHOULD</i>
<i>HAVE BEEN EXPLAINED AWAY,</i>

374
00:30:36,268 --> 00:30:38,402
<i>BUT MY LOGIC WOULDN'T.</i>

375
00:30:38,404 --> 00:30:40,304
<i>IT COULDN'T.</i>

376
00:30:41,906 --> 00:30:44,608
<i>AND MY FEAR CUT RIGHT</i>
<i>THROUGH THE PAIN OF DYING.</i>

377
00:30:46,578 --> 00:30:48,545
<i>MY REPUGNANCE</i>
<i>WAS SOON FORGOTTEN</i>

378
00:30:48,547 --> 00:30:51,515
<i>AS I WAS SWALLOWED</i>
<i>INTO A PEACEFUL BLACKNESS.</i>

379
00:30:51,517 --> 00:30:55,352
( electricity crackling )

380
00:30:55,354 --> 00:30:59,189
<i>HONESTLY,</i>
<i>DESPITE MY IRRATIONAL FEAR,</i>

381
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:01,525
<i>I SHOULD HAVE BEEN</i>
<i>IN ADMIRATION</i>

382
00:31:01,527 --> 00:31:03,527
<i>OF THE SURGEON'S GREAT SKILL.</i>

383
00:31:22,513 --> 00:31:24,381
WHAT ARE YOU NOW?

384
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:32,189
Mrs. Hayward:
<i>STAY AWAY FROM MY</i>
<i>DAUGHTER, MR. BAXTER.</i>

385
00:31:35,026 --> 00:31:36,493
Charlie:
<i>WHO AM I?</i>

386
00:31:36,495 --> 00:31:38,395
<i>( distorted humming )</i>

387
00:32:24,175 --> 00:32:26,410
<i>THE DOCTOR CLEARLY</i>
<i>UNDERSTOOD MY NEED</i>

388
00:32:26,412 --> 00:32:29,613
<i>AND ADMINISTERED TREATMENT</i>
<i>WITH A MASTER'S TOUCH,</i>

389
00:32:29,615 --> 00:32:33,283
<i>ALL THE WHILE REASSURING ME</i>
<i>IN A FINELY MODULATED</i>

390
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:35,485
<i>THOUGH ODDLY DEAD</i>
<i>AND TONELESS VOICE</i>

391
00:32:35,487 --> 00:32:39,089
<i>THAT THE DOCTOR WAS</i>
<i>THE SWORN ENEMY OF DEATH.</i>

392
00:32:39,091 --> 00:32:41,224
<i>AND HORRORS ASIDE,</i>

393
00:32:42,393 --> 00:32:44,461
<i>MY LIFE WAS SAVED.</i>

394
00:32:45,530 --> 00:32:47,597
<i>( soft whirring )</i>

395
00:32:50,401 --> 00:32:52,436
<i>WHEN I AWOKE</i>
<i>NINE HOURS LATER,</i>

396
00:32:52,438 --> 00:32:55,305
<i>I FOUND MYSELF</i>
<i>IN MY ROOM...</i>

397
00:32:57,208 --> 00:32:59,109
<i>WITH DR. SHOCKNER.</i>

398
00:33:01,412 --> 00:33:03,413
( weakly )
DOCTOR.

399
00:33:03,415 --> 00:33:05,048
( groans )

400
00:33:05,050 --> 00:33:07,551
( hoarsely )
I LIKED YOUR SCRIPT...

401
00:33:07,553 --> 00:33:10,320
ESPECIALLY ABOUT
THE MAD DOCTOR.

402
00:33:11,255 --> 00:33:13,023
IT'S JUST A SCRIPT.

403
00:33:13,025 --> 00:33:15,559
IT'S TRUE.
( clicks tongue )

404
00:33:15,561 --> 00:33:18,395
I AM CONSIDERED
QUITE MAD BY MOST...

405
00:33:18,397 --> 00:33:21,498
( whispers )
ESPECIALLY OTHER DOCTORS.

406
00:33:23,334 --> 00:33:25,268
WELL...

407
00:33:25,270 --> 00:33:26,770
I'LL VOUCH FOR YOU.

408
00:33:26,772 --> 00:33:29,039
<i>( crows cawing )</i>

409
00:33:31,709 --> 00:33:35,512
HOW DOES IT END,
YOUR SCRIPT?

410
00:33:38,716 --> 00:33:40,584
I DON'T KNOW.

411
00:33:42,153 --> 00:33:43,553
HAVE ANY IDEAS?

412
00:33:44,489 --> 00:33:46,456
ANY IDEAS?

413
00:33:49,193 --> 00:33:52,462
I AM ONE OF THOSE
WITH A COLD, CLINICAL MIND.

414
00:33:52,464 --> 00:33:55,132
NO SENTIMENTALITY.

415
00:33:55,134 --> 00:33:57,401
SOUNDS LIKE AN AGENT.

416
00:33:57,403 --> 00:33:59,436
( chuckling )

417
00:34:03,474 --> 00:34:06,610
DO YOU MIND GETTING
IDEAS FROM OTHERS?

418
00:34:07,812 --> 00:34:10,047
NOT WHEN THEY'VE
SAVED MY LIFE.

419
00:34:13,051 --> 00:34:15,185
ALL RIGHT THEN.

420
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:19,556
I THINK YOUR VILLAIN
NEEDS MORE HISTORY.

421
00:34:20,491 --> 00:34:22,793
THE DOCTOR'S
NOT A VILLAIN.

422
00:34:23,728 --> 00:34:25,395
REALLY?

423
00:34:26,330 --> 00:34:28,432
IT READS
THAT WAY TO ME.

424
00:34:28,434 --> 00:34:30,834
MISUNDERSTOOD.

425
00:34:33,471 --> 00:34:36,373
<i>ANYWAY, IT'S JUST</i>
<i>A FIRST DRAFT.</i>

426
00:34:38,443 --> 00:34:40,644
THERE'S ROOM
FOR CHANGE THEN?

427
00:34:40,646 --> 00:34:42,712
FOR THE STORY
OF THIS MAD DOCTOR

428
00:34:42,714 --> 00:34:44,514
TO GO IN ANOTHER
DIRECTION?

429
00:34:44,516 --> 00:34:46,616
SURE.

430
00:34:46,618 --> 00:34:48,518
REWRITES.

431
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:50,487
( chuckles )
FUN.

432
00:34:50,489 --> 00:34:52,456
( exhales )

433
00:34:53,524 --> 00:34:56,159
WHAT DID YOU HAVE
IN MIND, DOCTOR?

434
00:34:57,161 --> 00:34:59,329
AS I WAS SAYING,

435
00:34:59,331 --> 00:35:01,832
THE DOCTOR NEEDS
MORE HISTORY.

436
00:35:03,534 --> 00:35:05,235
SAY THIS DOCTOR,

437
00:35:05,237 --> 00:35:07,437
WHO WAS BRILLIANT
BEYOND WORDS,

438
00:35:07,439 --> 00:35:10,540
WAS SUDDENLY STRICKEN
WITH A RARE FATAL DISEASE.

439
00:35:10,542 --> 00:35:13,577
SHE COULDN'T ACCEPT
IMPENDING DEATH SO--

440
00:35:13,579 --> 00:35:15,545
"SHE"?

441
00:35:15,547 --> 00:35:18,615
MY MAD DOCTOR IS MALE.

442
00:35:21,519 --> 00:35:23,587
DID I SAY "SHE"?

443
00:35:23,589 --> 00:35:26,156
I'M SORRY.

444
00:35:26,158 --> 00:35:27,557
I MEANT "HE."

445
00:35:28,559 --> 00:35:31,528
BUT I LIKE
THE SEX CHANGE.

446
00:35:31,530 --> 00:35:35,632
- <i>DO YOU?</i>
<i>- VERY MUCH.</i>

447
00:35:35,634 --> 00:35:38,668
AS I SAID,
SHE COULDN'T ACCEPT DEATH.

448
00:35:40,872 --> 00:35:43,440
SHE WAS
A GREAT SURGEON,

449
00:35:43,442 --> 00:35:45,175
A BRILLIANT SURGEON.

450
00:35:45,177 --> 00:35:48,545
SHE WAS A LIFE-GIVER
WHEN THERE WAS NO HOPE.

451
00:35:50,581 --> 00:35:53,650
SHE HAD THE SKILLS
AND THE TALENTS OF GOD.

452
00:35:55,853 --> 00:35:57,654
SO SHE WAS...

453
00:35:58,623 --> 00:36:01,358
BIG INTO HER EGO AND...

454
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:03,160
SHE COULDN'T ACCEPT

455
00:36:03,162 --> 00:36:05,929
NOT BEING ABLE
TO SAVE HER OWN LIFE,

456
00:36:05,931 --> 00:36:08,632
HER OWN WORTHY LIFE,
WHEN SHE HAD SAVED

457
00:36:08,634 --> 00:36:10,800
SO MANY LESS VALUABLE,

458
00:36:10,802 --> 00:36:12,736
MY OWN INCLUDED.

459
00:36:13,704 --> 00:36:16,339
IN A SENSE, YES.

460
00:36:18,776 --> 00:36:20,677
I LIKE IT.

461
00:36:22,614 --> 00:36:26,783
SO THIS BRILLIANT DOCTOR
HAD TO SAVE HERSELF.

462
00:36:26,785 --> 00:36:30,353
SHE KNEW SHE COULD DO IT
BEFORE TIME WAS OUT.

463
00:36:30,355 --> 00:36:32,556
SHE SOON HAD SUNK
HER FORTUNE

464
00:36:32,558 --> 00:36:34,191
AND LOST ALL HER FRIENDS

465
00:36:34,193 --> 00:36:35,859
IN A YEAR
OF BIZARRE EXPERIMENTS

466
00:36:35,861 --> 00:36:37,794
DEVOTED TO CHEATING DEATH.

467
00:36:39,463 --> 00:36:42,332
Charlie's voice:
<i>SOMETHING OF THE BENEVOLENT</i>
<i>FANATIC</i>

468
00:36:42,334 --> 00:36:44,234
<i>SEEMED TO RESIDE</i>
<i>WITHIN HER,</i>

469
00:36:44,236 --> 00:36:47,470
<i>AND SHE RAMBLED ON</i>
<i>ALMOST GARRULOUSLY.</i>

470
00:36:52,743 --> 00:36:55,645
<i>EVIDENTLY SHE FOUND</i>
<i>THE SOCIETY OF A WELL-BORN,</i>

471
00:36:55,647 --> 00:36:58,248
<i>WELL-EDUCATED WOMAN</i>
<i>A RARE NOVELTY</i>

472
00:36:58,250 --> 00:37:00,717
<i>IN THIS SHALLOW WORLD</i>
<i>CALLED MALIBU,</i>

473
00:37:01,652 --> 00:37:04,554
<i>AND WAS MOVED TO MEMORIES</i>
<i>OF BETTER DAYS</i>

474
00:37:04,556 --> 00:37:08,725
<i>AT GRAND UNIVERSITIES</i>
<i>AND WORLD-RENOWNED</i>
<i>MEDICAL CLINICS.</i>

475
00:37:10,861 --> 00:37:13,496
<i>HER VOICE, IF QUEER,</i>

476
00:37:13,498 --> 00:37:15,498
<i>WAS AT LEAST SOOTHING.</i>

477
00:37:16,834 --> 00:37:19,769
<i>SHE SOUGHT TO DISTRACT MY MIND</i>
<i>FROM MY OWN BRUSH WITH DEATH</i>

478
00:37:19,771 --> 00:37:22,772
<i>BY SPEAKING OF HER THEORIES</i>
<i>AND EXPERIMENTS.</i>

479
00:37:23,941 --> 00:37:26,476
<i>AND I REMEMBER</i>
<i>HER TACTFULLY CONSOLING ME</i>

480
00:37:26,478 --> 00:37:28,478
<i>ABOUT MY WEAK HEART</i>

481
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:31,681
<i>BY INSISTING THAT</i>
<i>WILL AND CONSCIOUSNESS</i>

482
00:37:31,683 --> 00:37:34,751
<i>ARE STRONGER</i>
<i>THAN ORGANIC LIFE ITSELF,</i>

483
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:38,655
<i>SO THAT IF A BODY IS</i>
<i>ESSENTIALLY HEALTHY</i>

484
00:37:38,657 --> 00:37:41,258
<i>EXCEPT IN THE AREA</i>
<i>OF DISEASE,</i>

485
00:37:41,260 --> 00:37:43,893
<i>AND THAT THE HEALTHY ORGANS</i>
<i>AND BONE AND TISSUE</i>

486
00:37:43,895 --> 00:37:45,695
<i>ARE CAREFULLY PRESERVED,</i>

487
00:37:45,697 --> 00:37:49,432
<i>IT MAY, THROUGH SCIENTIFIC</i>
<i>ENHANCEMENT,</i>

488
00:37:49,434 --> 00:37:51,668
<i>RETAIN A KIND OF ANIMATION</i>

489
00:37:51,670 --> 00:37:54,704
<i>DESPITE THE MOST SERIOUS</i>
<i>IMPAIRMENTS, DEFECTS,</i>

490
00:37:54,706 --> 00:37:57,874
<i>OR EVEN ABSENCES</i>
<i>OF MAJOR ORGANS.</i>

491
00:37:57,876 --> 00:37:59,576
<i>( heart beating )</i>

492
00:37:59,578 --> 00:38:03,413
<i>SHE MIGHT,</i>
<i>SHE HALF-JOKED,</i>

493
00:38:03,415 --> 00:38:05,682
<i>SOME DAY</i>
<i>TEACH ME TO LIVE--</i>

494
00:38:05,684 --> 00:38:09,486
<i>OR AT LEAST TO POSSESS</i>
<i>SOME KIND OF CONSCIOUS</i>
<i>EXISTENCE</i>

495
00:38:10,588 --> 00:38:12,622
<i>WITHOUT ANY HEART AT ALL.</i>

496
00:38:13,924 --> 00:38:15,625
WHAT?

497
00:38:22,867 --> 00:38:25,802
NO HEART AT ALL?

498
00:38:27,405 --> 00:38:28,772
YOU MEAN...

499
00:38:29,740 --> 00:38:31,508
WITH AN ARTIFICIAL HEART

500
00:38:31,510 --> 00:38:34,511
OR SOME KIND
OF A MACHINE?

501
00:38:34,513 --> 00:38:35,745
NO.

502
00:38:35,747 --> 00:38:37,914
WITHOUT ANY PUMP.

503
00:38:37,916 --> 00:38:41,785
BUT THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE,
ISN'T IT?

504
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:45,689
<i>DEFYING THE LAWS</i>
<i>OF PHYSICS</i>

505
00:38:45,691 --> 00:38:47,791
<i>OR GOD OR SOMETHING.</i>

506
00:38:47,793 --> 00:38:49,759
OR SOMETHING, YES.

507
00:38:49,761 --> 00:38:51,728
THAT WOULD BE IT.

508
00:38:54,398 --> 00:38:57,801
IS THIS TOO MUCH
FOR YOUR SCREENPLAY?

509
00:38:57,803 --> 00:39:01,838
I DON'T KNOW
IF THE AUDIENCE CAN
SUSPEND THEIR DISBELIEF.

510
00:39:04,608 --> 00:39:06,676
I'M NOT SURE I CAN.

511
00:39:09,780 --> 00:39:11,781
I KNOW THE STUDIOS
WOULDN'T.

512
00:39:11,783 --> 00:39:13,583
( guffaws )
REALLY?

513
00:39:14,852 --> 00:39:18,922
I WASN'T AWARE THAT
"NIGHT OF THE LIVING DEAD"
WAS A DOCUMENTARY.

514
00:39:20,524 --> 00:39:22,525
TELL ME ALL OF IT.

515
00:39:22,527 --> 00:39:24,728
I'M SORRY
I INTERRUPTED.

516
00:39:26,764 --> 00:39:28,965
Charlie's voice:
FOR HER PART, SHE WAS AFFLICTED

517
00:39:28,967 --> 00:39:31,067
<i>WITH A COMPLICATION</i>
<i>OF DISEASES</i>

518
00:39:31,069 --> 00:39:33,002
<i>REQUIRING</i>
<i>A VERY EXACT REGIMEN,</i>

519
00:39:33,004 --> 00:39:35,004
<i>WHICH INCLUDED</i>
<i>CONSTANT COLD.</i>

520
00:39:36,574 --> 00:39:39,042
<i>IT WAS THEN I NOTICED</i>
<i>THE TEMPERATURE IN MY ROOM.</i>

521
00:39:40,511 --> 00:39:42,078
<i>IT WAS COLD.</i>

522
00:39:43,814 --> 00:39:47,517
<i>I NOTICED THE AIR CONDITIONER</i>
<i>IN MY ROOM GOING FULL POWER.</i>

523
00:39:48,819 --> 00:39:51,421
<i>FUNNY, I HADN'T</i>
<i>NOTICED IT BEFORE.</i>

524
00:39:52,723 --> 00:39:55,392
<i>SHE SAID ANY MARKED RISE</i>
<i>IN TEMPERATURE MIGHT,</i>

525
00:39:55,394 --> 00:39:58,027
<i>IF PROLONGED,</i>
<i>AFFECT HER FATALLY;</i>

526
00:39:58,029 --> 00:40:00,830
<i>AND THE COLDNESS</i>
<i>OF HER ROOM--</i>

527
00:40:00,832 --> 00:40:04,167
<i>SOME 55째</i>
<i>OR 56째 FAHRENHEIT--</i>

528
00:40:04,169 --> 00:40:09,439
- <i>HER AIR CONDITIONER HAD</i>
<i>ADDITIONAL BATTERIES...</i>
<i>- ( Shockner coughing )</i>

529
00:40:09,441 --> 00:40:11,007
<i>...AND AN AIR-CLEANING PUMP.</i>

530
00:40:11,009 --> 00:40:13,076
<i>THAT WAS THE SOUND</i>
<i>I HAD HEARD IN MY OWN ROOM.</i>

531
00:40:13,078 --> 00:40:16,079
( wheezes )

532
00:40:16,081 --> 00:40:18,148
( coughing continues )

533
00:40:20,117 --> 00:40:21,918
( weakly )
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

534
00:40:24,922 --> 00:40:26,689
I JUST NEED TO REST...

535
00:40:27,858 --> 00:40:28,958
( whispers )
IN MY ROOM.

536
00:40:30,027 --> 00:40:32,495
( inhales sharply, thuds )

537
00:40:35,199 --> 00:40:37,867
- ( inhales sharply )
- AM I ALL RIGHT?

538
00:40:37,869 --> 00:40:39,936
( sighs )

539
00:40:41,172 --> 00:40:43,940
YOU MEAN, SHOULD YOU
GO TO THE HOSPITAL?

540
00:40:43,942 --> 00:40:45,942
- ( inhales sharply )
- YES.

541
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:49,479
ONLY IF YOU WANT TO DIE.

542
00:40:50,881 --> 00:40:53,149
THEN I'M OKAY?
( swallows )

543
00:40:53,151 --> 00:40:54,951
FOR REAL?

544
00:40:55,886 --> 00:40:57,720
YOU'RE FINE.

545
00:40:59,890 --> 00:41:01,758
JUST REST.

546
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:03,660
STAY IN BED.

547
00:41:05,563 --> 00:41:08,131
DO NOT LET
THE SUNLIGHT IN.

548
00:41:11,135 --> 00:41:14,137
( exhales )
I'LL COME TO SEE YOU
IN THE AFTERNOON.

549
00:41:15,906 --> 00:41:17,607
OKAY.

550
00:41:18,542 --> 00:41:19,976
YOU'RE THE DOCTOR.

551
00:41:21,912 --> 00:41:23,179
I MEAN IT, CHARLIE.

552
00:41:24,114 --> 00:41:26,249
DO NOT LEAVE THIS ROOM.

553
00:41:27,818 --> 00:41:29,719
ALL RIGHT,

554
00:41:29,721 --> 00:41:31,921
BUT MRS. HAYWARD IS
GONNA BE PISSED.

555
00:41:31,923 --> 00:41:33,590
<i>SHE EVICTED ME.</i>

556
00:41:34,892 --> 00:41:37,494
I'VE ADDRESSED IT.

557
00:41:37,496 --> 00:41:40,230
YOU'RE FREE TO STAY
UNTIL YOU'RE FULLY RECOVERED.

558
00:41:41,732 --> 00:41:43,700
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

559
00:41:43,702 --> 00:41:45,268
I JUST REMINDED HER

560
00:41:45,270 --> 00:41:49,005
OF THE HIGH COST
OF LIABILITY LAWSUITS.

561
00:41:50,975 --> 00:41:53,076
GOOD NIGHT, CHARLIE.

562
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:55,745
GOOD NIGHT.

563
00:41:56,981 --> 00:41:58,548
THANK YOU.

564
00:42:01,018 --> 00:42:03,019
( whispers )
OH, IT'S MY PLEASURE.

565
00:42:05,289 --> 00:42:07,757
NICE TO HAVE
A COMPANION.

566
00:42:09,960 --> 00:42:12,028
<i>( pump hissing )</i>

567
00:42:16,967 --> 00:42:19,035
<i>( ascending footsteps )</i>

568
00:42:28,879 --> 00:42:30,980
Charlie's voice:
<i>RELIEVED OF MY HEART FAILURE</i>

569
00:42:30,982 --> 00:42:33,683
<i>IN AN INCREDIBLY SHORT TIME,</i>

570
00:42:33,685 --> 00:42:35,685
<i>I FELL ASLEEP,</i>

571
00:42:35,687 --> 00:42:38,988
<i>A DISCIPLE AND DEVOTEE</i>
<i>OF THE GIFTED RECLUSE.</i>

572
00:42:39,990 --> 00:42:41,991
<i>( knocks on door )</i>

573
00:42:41,993 --> 00:42:44,060
COME IN.

574
00:42:46,997 --> 00:42:48,631
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

575
00:42:49,767 --> 00:42:52,068
I'VE BEEN BETTER,
THAT'S FOR SURE.

576
00:42:54,338 --> 00:42:56,272
THANKS FOR
LETTING ME STAY.

577
00:42:56,274 --> 00:42:57,941
GLAD TO HAVE YOU.

578
00:42:57,943 --> 00:43:03,012
THE DOCTOR SAID
THAT YOU'LL BE WEAK
FOR A FEW MORE WEEKS.

579
00:43:03,014 --> 00:43:05,882
I FEEL LIKE I'VE BEEN
RUN OVER BY A TRUCK.

580
00:43:05,884 --> 00:43:08,017
SHE SAID TO MAKE SURE THAT
YOU HAVE PLENTY OF REST,

581
00:43:08,019 --> 00:43:11,020
THAT YOU EAT A GOOD MEAL.
SHE MADE THIS HERSELF.

582
00:43:11,022 --> 00:43:12,622
YEAH, REST.

583
00:43:12,624 --> 00:43:15,291
REST-- REST AND,
UH, FOOD.  YEAH.

584
00:43:15,293 --> 00:43:18,027
( stammers )

585
00:43:18,029 --> 00:43:20,196
THE... DOCTOR--
DOCTOR KNOWS.

586
00:43:20,198 --> 00:43:22,799
YEAH, THE DOCTOR KNOWS.
DOCTOR KNOWS.  DOCTOR KNOWS.

587
00:43:22,801 --> 00:43:24,734
THAT-- THAT'S RIGHT.
YES, THE DOCTOR KNOWS.

588
00:43:24,736 --> 00:43:26,369
THANKS.

589
00:43:27,871 --> 00:43:30,073
WELL, IF THERE'S ANYTHING
YOU WANT, LET US KNOW.

590
00:43:30,075 --> 00:43:32,241
- COME ON, ESTELLA.
- OH YEAH, MAMA, YEAH.

591
00:43:32,243 --> 00:43:34,344
I CAN-- I CAN--
I CAN, UH--

592
00:43:34,346 --> 00:43:36,045
I CAN FEED HIM, YEAH.

593
00:43:36,047 --> 00:43:38,948
'CAUSE-'CAUSE--
YEAH, HE-- HE MUST EAT.

594
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:41,384
YEAH, AND I CAN-- I CAN--
I CAN FEED HIM, YEAH.

595
00:43:41,386 --> 00:43:44,954
ALL RIGHT.  SLOWLY.

596
00:43:44,956 --> 00:43:48,057
MR. BAXTER'S SYSTEM
MAY NOT BE QUITE RIGHT YET.

597
00:43:48,059 --> 00:43:50,059
OH YEAH, MAMA,
