<i>AND THIS WOULD TAKE WEEKS--</i>

814
00:56:45,035 --> 00:56:46,835
<i>ESTELLA WOULD FIND HIM</i>

815
00:56:46,837 --> 00:56:49,104
<i>LYING IN THE FREEZER</i>
<i>WITH HIS DEAD WIFE.</i>

816
00:56:49,106 --> 00:56:50,873
<i>HE SLIT HIS WRISTS</i>

817
00:56:50,875 --> 00:56:53,909
<i>AND WRAPPED HIS BLOODY PAWS</i>
<i>AROUND HIS LOVING WIFE.</i>

818
00:57:05,855 --> 00:57:08,590
<i>THERE WAS AN INCREASING</i>
<i>AND UNEXPLAINED ATMOSPHERE</i>

819
00:57:08,592 --> 00:57:11,693
<i>OF EVIL AND HORROR</i>
<i>THAT SEEMED TO RISE</i>
<i>AROUND THE HAYWARD HOUSE.</i>

820
00:57:12,862 --> 00:57:14,863
<i>THE WHOLE HOUSE,</i>
<i>AS I'VE SAID,</i>

821
00:57:14,865 --> 00:57:16,865
<i>HAD A MUSTY ODOR.</i>

822
00:57:16,867 --> 00:57:19,868
<i>BUT THE SMELL</i>
<i>THIS DAY WAS WORSE.</i>

823
00:57:19,870 --> 00:57:22,938
<i>AND IN SPITE OF ALL</i>
<i>THE DEODORIZER AND INCENSE,</i>

824
00:57:22,940 --> 00:57:25,674
<i>AND THE PUNGENT</i>
<i>CLEANING CHEMICALS,</i>

825
00:57:25,676 --> 00:57:28,944
<i>IT WOULD BE A SMELL</i>
<i>THAT WOULD NEVER BE MASKED.</i>

826
00:57:32,982 --> 00:57:34,983
<i>FIENDISH THINGS WERE</i>
<i>IN THE AIR.</i>

827
00:57:36,486 --> 00:57:39,655
<i>SO STRONG WAS</i>
<i>THE PUNGENT PRESENCE OF EVIL</i>

828
00:57:39,657 --> 00:57:41,890
<i>THAT BELIEVERS</i>
<i>WOULD BE REACHING WILDLY</i>

829
00:57:41,892 --> 00:57:44,059
<i>FOR THE BEADS</i>
<i>OF THEIR ROSARIES.</i>

830
00:57:44,061 --> 00:57:47,095
<i>A LESS ADVENTURESOME SOUL</i>
<i>WOULD HAVE LONG FLED,</i>

831
00:57:47,097 --> 00:57:48,931
<i>SCREAMING AND MAD-EYED.</i>

832
00:57:48,933 --> 00:57:51,900
<i>THERE WAS NO SOUND</i>
<i>WITHIN THE GREAT HOUSE,</i>

833
00:57:51,902 --> 00:57:56,839
<i>EXCEPT A NAMELESS</i>
<i>SORT OF SLOW, THICK DRIPPING.</i>

834
00:57:57,907 --> 00:58:00,576
<i>( door opens )</i>

835
00:58:13,223 --> 00:58:15,824
<i>THE SOUNDS WERE</i>
<i>OF UTTER TURMOIL.</i>

836
00:58:15,826 --> 00:58:19,261
<i>AND ABOVE THE CLATTERING</i>
<i>AND SLAMMING OF ODD VOICES,</i>

837
00:58:19,263 --> 00:58:22,264
<i>I HEARD A WOMAN PRAYING</i>
<i>IN A DESPERATE PLEA.</i>

838
00:58:22,266 --> 00:58:24,233
<i>IT WAS THE DOCTOR.</i>

839
00:58:24,235 --> 00:58:26,668
<i>WE COULD HEAR</i>
<i>A WILD THRASHING</i>

840
00:58:26,670 --> 00:58:27,836
<i>WITHIN THE DOCTOR'S ROOM</i>

841
00:58:27,838 --> 00:58:29,972
<i>AND A HYSTERICAL VOICE</i>
<i>CROAKING,</i>

842
00:58:29,974 --> 00:58:32,674
<i>"THE COLD.  THE COLD."</i>

843
00:58:32,676 --> 00:58:36,245
- <i>( Shockner moaning )</i>
<i>- HER AIR CONDITIONING FAILED.</i>

844
00:58:36,247 --> 00:58:39,748
SHE NEEDS HELP!
LISTEN TO HER!

845
00:58:40,683 --> 00:58:41,850
IT'S A PITY.

846
00:58:43,686 --> 00:58:45,687
Charlie's voice:
<i>AS I TRIED TO WALK,</i>

847
00:58:45,689 --> 00:58:48,857
<i>I WAS SUDDENLY AWARE</i>
<i>OF HOW WARM IT WAS</i>
<i>IN THE HALL.</i>

848
00:58:48,859 --> 00:58:50,692
<i>IT MADE ME DIZZY AND WEAK</i>

849
00:58:50,694 --> 00:58:52,828
<i>AND SICK TO MY STOMACH.</i>

850
00:58:52,830 --> 00:58:55,297
<i>I NEEDED THE COLD.</i>

851
00:59:00,570 --> 00:59:02,204
<i>THE DOCTOR'S</i>
<i>RAGE AND FEAR,</i>

852
00:59:02,206 --> 00:59:04,740
<i>SWELLING</i>
<i>TO GROTESQUE PROPORTIONS,</i>

853
00:59:04,742 --> 00:59:08,610
<i>SEEMED LIKELY</i>
<i>TO SHATTER WHAT REMAINED</i>
<i>OF HER FAILING PHYSIQUE.</i>

854
00:59:08,612 --> 00:59:11,013
<i>AND ONCE A SPASM CAUSED HER</i>
<i>TO CLAP HER HANDS</i>

855
00:59:11,015 --> 00:59:13,215
<i>TO HER EYES</i>
<i>TO SHIELD THEM...</i>

856
00:59:13,217 --> 00:59:15,717
<i>OR KEEP THEM</i>
<i>FROM FALLING OUT.</i>

857
00:59:16,953 --> 00:59:19,187
<i>SHE GROPED HER WAY</i>
<i>DOWN THE HALL TOWARD ME</i>

858
00:59:19,189 --> 00:59:21,123
<i>AS IF BLIND</i>
<i>FOR THE FIRST TIME.</i>

859
00:59:23,293 --> 00:59:25,794
<i>THE DOCTOR'S STENCH</i>
<i>WAS OVER-POWERING.</i>

860
00:59:27,030 --> 00:59:29,097
<i>IT WAS SO STRONG</i>
<i>AS TO SUCK THE OXYGEN</i>

861
00:59:29,099 --> 00:59:30,732
<i>OUT OF THE AIR.</i>

862
00:59:30,734 --> 00:59:33,235
<i>I FELT SUFFOCATED</i>
<i>AND SMOTHERED BY IT.</i>

863
00:59:34,737 --> 00:59:36,805
<i>AGAINST ALL</i>
<i>MY SCREAMING INSTINCTS,</i>

864
00:59:37,907 --> 00:59:39,808
<i>I REACHED OUT</i>
<i>TO THIS POOR WOMAN.</i>

865
00:59:42,278 --> 00:59:44,680
( labored breathing )

866
01:00:17,246 --> 01:00:19,648
<i>AS THE MINUTES PASSED</i>

867
01:00:19,650 --> 01:00:22,050
<i>I OBSERVED WITH REGRET</i>
<i>THAT MY NEW FRIEND</i>

868
01:00:22,052 --> 01:00:25,053
<i>WAS INDEED SLOWLY,</i>
<i>BUT UNMISTAKABLY</i>

869
01:00:25,055 --> 01:00:27,189
<i>LOOSING GROUND</i>
<i>PHYSICALLY.</i>

870
01:00:27,191 --> 01:00:30,959
<i>THE LIVID ASPECT</i>
<i>OF HER BEING WAS INTENSIFIED.</i>

871
01:00:30,961 --> 01:00:34,696
<i>HER VOICE BECAME</i>
<i>MORE HOLLOW AND INDISTINCT.</i>

872
01:00:34,698 --> 01:00:38,300
<i>HER GRACEFUL MOTIONS WERE</i>
<i>LESS PERFECTLY COORDINATED.</i>

873
01:00:38,302 --> 01:00:40,268
<i>AND HER MIND AND WILL</i>

874
01:00:40,270 --> 01:00:43,672
<i>DISPLAYED LESS RESILIENCE</i>
<i>AND INITIATIVE.</i>

875
01:00:45,808 --> 01:00:47,809
( hoarsely )
DO I DISGUST YOU?

876
01:00:48,978 --> 01:00:52,114
- NO.
- <i>SHE WAS AWARE</i>
<i>OF THIS SAD CHANGE</i>

877
01:00:52,116 --> 01:00:54,883
<i>AND LITTLE BY LITTLE</i>
<i>HER EXPRESSION AND CONVERSATION</i>

878
01:00:54,885 --> 01:00:58,320
<i>BOTH TOOK ON A GRUESOME IRONY</i>
<i>WHICH RESTORED IN ME...</i>

879
01:00:58,322 --> 01:01:00,155
NOT EXACTLY.

880
01:01:00,157 --> 01:01:02,190
<i>...SOMETHING</i>
<i>OF THE SUBTLE REPULSION</i>

881
01:01:02,192 --> 01:01:04,059
<i>I HAD ORIGINALLY FELT.</i>

882
01:01:04,061 --> 01:01:06,662
MMM.  IT'S THE SMELL.

883
01:01:08,798 --> 01:01:10,666
NOW THAT YOU MENTION IT.

884
01:01:20,443 --> 01:01:22,711
I WAS BEAUTIFUL.

885
01:01:23,680 --> 01:01:25,447
I CAN SEE THAT.

886
01:01:30,386 --> 01:01:32,888
- ( sizzling )
- ( labored breathing )

887
01:01:37,060 --> 01:01:38,360
IT'S...

888
01:01:39,796 --> 01:01:41,396
IT'S TIME FOR--

889
01:01:41,398 --> 01:01:44,199
FOR YOU TO TAKE
YOUR MEDS.

890
01:01:49,038 --> 01:01:52,174
YOU HAVE A CHOICE,
CHARLIE.

891
01:01:54,877 --> 01:01:56,344
A CHOICE?

892
01:01:59,348 --> 01:02:01,483
A CHOICE.

893
01:02:03,886 --> 01:02:06,154
ONE I DID NOT HAVE.

894
01:02:08,391 --> 01:02:10,492
TELL ME
ABOUT MY CHOICE...

895
01:02:11,794 --> 01:02:13,295
AND YOURS.

896
01:02:20,002 --> 01:02:22,904
Charlie's voice:
<i>I LISTENED, ADDICTED</i>
<i>TO HER EVERY WORD.</i>

897
01:02:22,906 --> 01:02:24,740
<i>( Shockner speaking )</i>

898
01:02:24,742 --> 01:02:26,908
Charlie's voice:
<i>SHE TOLD OF SECRET RESEARCHES</i>

899
01:02:26,910 --> 01:02:28,744
<i>AND ALMOST GHASTLY RESULTS.</i>

900
01:02:29,979 --> 01:02:32,481
<i>IT SEEMS THAT SHE DID NOT</i>
<i>SCORN THE INCANTATIONS</i>

901
01:02:32,483 --> 01:02:34,249
<i>OF THE WITCHES</i>
<i>AND THE BLACK ARTS</i>

902
01:02:34,251 --> 01:02:36,918
<i>WITH REGARD</i>
<i>TO LIFE AND DEATH,</i>

903
01:02:36,920 --> 01:02:39,054
<i>SINCE SHE BELIEVED</i>
<i>THESE CRYPTIC ARTS</i>

904
01:02:39,056 --> 01:02:41,256
<i>CONTAINED RARE</i>
<i>PSYCHOLOGICAL STIMULI</i>

905
01:02:41,258 --> 01:02:43,925
<i>WHICH MIGHT CONCEIVABLY</i>
<i>HAVE HEALING EFFECTS</i>

906
01:02:43,927 --> 01:02:47,295
<i>ON THE NERVOUS SYSTEM</i>
<i>IN WHICH ORGANIC LIFE HAD DIED.</i>

907
01:02:50,500 --> 01:02:54,936
<i>I WAS MOVED BY HER ACCOUNT</i>
<i>OF THE AGED DR. TORRES</i>
<i>OF VALENCIA, SPAIN,</i>

908
01:02:54,938 --> 01:02:57,939
<i>WHO HAD SHARED</i>
<i>HIS EARLIER EXPERIMENTS</i>

909
01:02:57,941 --> 01:03:00,342
<i>AND NURSED DR. SHOCKNER</i>
<i>THROUGH A GREAT ILLNESS</i>

910
01:03:00,344 --> 01:03:02,210
<i>18 YEARS BEFORE,</i>

911
01:03:02,212 --> 01:03:04,880
<i>AND WHERE HER</i>
<i>PRESENT DISORDERS BEGAN.</i>

912
01:03:04,882 --> 01:03:06,314
...BEYOND MY TIME...

913
01:03:06,316 --> 01:03:09,217
<i>NO SOONER HAD</i>
<i>DR. TORRES SAVE HIS COLLEAGUE</i>

914
01:03:09,219 --> 01:03:13,388
<i>THAT HE HIMSELF DIED</i>
<i>A GRIM DEATH IN A FIRE.</i>

915
01:03:13,390 --> 01:03:16,158
<i>THE DOCTOR MADE IT</i>
<i>WHISPERINGLY CLEAR--</i>

916
01:03:16,160 --> 01:03:18,160
<i>THOUGH NOT IN DETAIL--</i>

917
01:03:18,162 --> 01:03:20,796
<i>THAT THE METHODS</i>
<i>TORRES USED TO HEAL</i>

918
01:03:20,798 --> 01:03:23,865
<i>HAD EXTRAORDINARY</i>
<i>INVOLVING TECHNIQUES</i>

919
01:03:23,867 --> 01:03:25,834
<i>AND PROCESSES NOT WELCOMED</i>

920
01:03:25,836 --> 01:03:27,969
<i>BY THE CONSERVATIVE WORLD</i>
<i>OF MODERN MEDICINE.</i>

921
01:03:27,971 --> 01:03:29,504
( coughing )

922
01:03:29,506 --> 01:03:33,809
- MRS. HAYWARD!  HELP!
- <i>...FOR HER TO CALL</i>
<i>THE PARAMEDICS.</i>

923
01:03:33,811 --> 01:03:35,343
-  <i>AS I LISTENED AT THE DOOR...</i>
<i>- WE NEED HELP!</i>

924
01:03:35,345 --> 01:03:38,480
<i>...I COULD HEAR</i>
<i>THE LANDLADY HUMMING</i>
<i>LIKE A CRAZY LOON.</i>

925
01:03:38,482 --> 01:03:40,115
- ( coughing continues )
- WE NEED HELP!

926
01:03:40,117 --> 01:03:42,984
<i>A KIND OF GROWING HORROR</i>
<i>SEEMED TO POSSESS HER.</i>

927
01:03:42,986 --> 01:03:44,853
CHARLIE!

928
01:03:44,855 --> 01:03:46,555
<i>SHE TALKED</i>
<i>ABOUT DEATH INCESSANTLY,</i>

929
01:03:47,857 --> 01:03:49,157
<i>BUT LAUGHED HOLLOWLY</i>

930
01:03:49,159 --> 01:03:51,827
<i>AT SUCH THINGS AS BURIAL</i>
<i>OR FUNERAL ARRANGEMENTS.</i>

931
01:03:51,829 --> 01:03:53,995
- YOU NEED HELP.
- ( labored breathing )

932
01:03:53,997 --> 01:03:56,498
YOU NEED HELP.
LET ME CALL THE PARAMEDICS.

933
01:03:58,000 --> 01:04:00,468
<i>THERE WAS SOME BITTER IRONY</i>
<i>IN THOSE MATTERS.</i>

934
01:04:04,006 --> 01:04:06,608
<i>ALL IN ALL,</i>
<i>SHE BECAME A DISCONCERTING</i>

935
01:04:06,610 --> 01:04:09,611
- <i>AND EVEN GRUESOME</i>
<i>COMPANION.</i>
<i>- PLEASE.</i>

936
01:04:09,613 --> 01:04:12,047
<i>YET MY GRATITUDE</i>
<i>FOR HER SAVING MY LIFE</i>

937
01:04:12,049 --> 01:04:14,216
<i>MADE IT IMPOSSIBLE</i>
<i>TO ABANDON HER.</i>

938
01:04:14,218 --> 01:04:15,417
OKAY.

939
01:04:18,454 --> 01:04:21,323
BUT FIRST, I NEED
TO WRITE SOMETHING.

940
01:04:30,099 --> 01:04:32,400
OKAY, TAKE--
TAKE YOUR TABLET NOW.

941
01:04:32,402 --> 01:04:34,469
( labored breathing )

942
01:04:38,107 --> 01:04:40,175
( coughing )

943
01:04:48,050 --> 01:04:50,118
( labored breathing )

944
01:05:20,082 --> 01:05:22,083
<i>SHE HAD WRAPPED</i>
<i>THE SCARF IN A WAY</i>

945
01:05:22,085 --> 01:05:24,286
<i>THAT HER EYES WERE HIDDEN</i>
<i>FROM MY VIEW.</i>

946
01:05:25,254 --> 01:05:27,422
<i>I NEVER SAW</i>
<i>HER EYES AGAIN.</i>

947
01:05:44,106 --> 01:05:45,473
<i>THE FIRST THING I NOTICED</i>

948
01:05:45,475 --> 01:05:47,642
<i>WAS THE COLDNESS</i>
<i>OF THE ROOM WAS GONE.</i>

949
01:05:49,111 --> 01:05:52,113
<i>THE SECOND THING I NOTICED</i>
<i>WAS IT WAS QUIET.</i>

950
01:05:53,115 --> 01:05:55,283
<i>THE AIR HAD</i>
<i>BEEN TURNED OFF.</i>

951
01:05:55,285 --> 01:05:58,253
<i>WHAT WAS, OR HAD BEEN,</i>

952
01:05:58,255 --> 01:06:01,957
<i>ON THE BED I CAN'T</i>
<i>AND DARE NOT SAY HERE.</i>

953
01:06:03,426 --> 01:06:06,394
<i>IT WAS HIDEOUS AND IT</i>
<i>WOULD HAUNT ME FOREVER.</i>

954
01:06:08,331 --> 01:06:11,533
<i>A CLAW-LIKE FINGER</i>
<i>POINTED ME TO THE TABLET.</i>

955
01:06:11,535 --> 01:06:14,469
<i>SOMETHING WAS</i>
<i>SCRAWLED IN PEN,</i>

956
01:06:14,471 --> 01:06:18,406
<i>IN AN AWFUL,</i>
<i>FRANTIC HANDWRITING</i>
<i>ON A PIECE OF PAPER</i>

957
01:06:18,408 --> 01:06:20,475
<i>HIDEOUSLY SMEARED</i>
<i>WITH OOZING ROT</i>

958
01:06:20,477 --> 01:06:23,278
<i>AS THOUGH BY THE VERY CLAW</i>
<i>THAT TRACED</i>

959
01:06:23,280 --> 01:06:25,280
<i>THE HURRIED LAST WORDS.</i>

960
01:06:27,383 --> 01:06:30,485
<i>IT WAS THE UTTER END</i>
<i>OF DR. SHOCKNER.</i>

961
01:06:35,291 --> 01:06:37,759
Shockner's voice:
<i>"THE END IS HERE.</i>

962
01:06:37,761 --> 01:06:40,061
<i>NO MORE THE SMELL</i>
<i>OF AMMONIA</i>

963
01:06:40,063 --> 01:06:43,031
<i>AND THE DESPERATE NEED</i>
<i>OF UNUSUALLY COOL AIR.</i>

964
01:06:44,166 --> 01:06:46,167
<i>IT'S GROWING WARMER</i>
<i>EVERY MINUTE</i>

965
01:06:46,169 --> 01:06:48,336
<i>AND THE TISSUES CAN'T LAST.</i>

966
01:06:49,338 --> 01:06:51,006
<i>THERE WAS AND IS</i>

967
01:06:51,008 --> 01:06:54,009
<i>A GRADUAL, INEVITABLE</i>
<i>DETERIORATION.</i>

968
01:06:54,011 --> 01:06:56,778
<i>DR. TORRES KNEW THIS.</i>

969
01:06:56,780 --> 01:07:00,248
<i>HE COULDN'T STAND</i>
<i>WHAT HE HAD CREATED IN ME.</i>

970
01:07:01,350 --> 01:07:03,184
<i>FOR YOU SEE,</i>

971
01:07:03,186 --> 01:07:07,589
<i>I DIED THAT TIME,</i>
<i>127 YEARS AGO."</i>

972
01:07:14,597 --> 01:07:16,664
- ( engine revs )
- ( gate rattles )

973
01:07:27,410 --> 01:07:28,610
( rattles )

974
01:08:03,412 --> 01:08:05,080
<i>( gate rattles )</i>

975
01:08:22,698 --> 01:08:25,266
Shockner's voice:
"NOW IT PASSES TO YOU, CHARLIE.

976
01:08:25,268 --> 01:08:27,335
<i>THE SECRETS.</i>

977
01:08:30,272 --> 01:08:32,240
<i>HOW FAR WOULD YOU GO</i>

978
01:08:32,242 --> 01:08:34,576
<i>TO REMAIN</i>
<i>AMONG THE LIVING?"</i>

979
01:08:41,283 --> 01:08:43,351
<i>( bangs )</i>

980
01:08:45,121 --> 01:08:46,721
Charlie's voice:
<i>YOU ASKED ME TO EXPLAIN</i>

981
01:08:46,723 --> 01:08:49,791
<i>WHY I'M AFRAID</i>
<i>OF A DRAFT OF COOL AIR,</i>

982
01:08:49,793 --> 01:08:53,328
<i>WHY I SHIVER MORE THAN OTHERS</i>
<i>WHEN I ENTER A COLD ROOM,</i>

983
01:08:53,330 --> 01:08:56,698
<i>WHY I SEEM SICK AND SCARED</i>
<i>WHEN THE CHILL OF EVENING</i>

984
01:08:56,700 --> 01:08:59,434
<i>CREEPS THROUGH THE HEAT</i>
<i>OF A MILD AUTUMN DAY.</i>

985
01:09:00,769 --> 01:09:02,871
<i>THERE ARE THOSE WHO SAY</i>
<i>I RESPOND TO COLD</i>

986
01:09:02,873 --> 01:09:05,507
<i>LIKE SOME DO</i>
<i>TO A BAD SMELL,</i>

987
01:09:05,509 --> 01:09:08,309
<i>AND I'M THE LAST</i>
<i>TO DENY THE IMPRESSION.</i>

988
01:09:08,311 --> 01:09:11,913
<i>MORE AND MORE I FEEL DRAWN</i>
<i>TO THE COOLNESS.</i>

989
01:09:11,915 --> 01:09:15,250
<i>MORE AND MORE I FEAR</i>
<i>I WILL NEED THE COOL AIR.</i>

990
01:09:16,352 --> 01:09:19,554
<i>A HAUNTING REMINDER</i>
<i>OF MY VULNERABILITY.</i>

991
01:09:21,223 --> 01:09:24,325
<i>WHAT I WILL DO IS TO RELATE</i>
<i>THE MOST HORRIBLE CIRCUMSTANCES</i>

992
01:09:24,327 --> 01:09:26,895
<i>I HAVE EVER EXPERIENCED</i>

993
01:09:26,897 --> 01:09:29,364
<i>AND LEAVE IT TO YOU</i>
<i>TO JUDGE WHETHER OR NOT</i>

994
01:09:29,366 --> 01:09:32,834
<i>THIS FORMS A SUITABLE</i>
<i>EXPLANATION OF MY WEIRDNESS</i>

